                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I am not advocating the lawsuit, but those of you who are poo pooing it out of the gate apparently don't pay much attention to the legal system in the United States.
<br />

<br />
There are court cases much more idiotic than this one that are argued every day, and they frequently win.  You read about them and think, "Damn, that was stupid!  What court would hear a case like that?"
<br />

<br />
This type of case would also get that kind of review, but it certainly isn't a doomed outcome.  I could very easily see a less than honest lawyer (as if there is any other kind) making a case not only out of the cost of the expansion itself, but putting a value on all the time invested in the characters that is now wasted.  If you think about it, even a dollar an hour /played for all enchanters on all servers is a healthy sum, plus monthly fees and all other expansions.  It is a persistent world, and character building is its foundation.  The enchanters already built have no real value in the current game, and this is due to recent changes.
<br />

<br />
Again, I am not advocating any of this, but don't think for a minute that a case could not be made, and the EULA doesn't protect Sony any more than the court allows it to.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
